m_q.target_metric: Average latitude of capital cities, with only one capital per country (the one with largest population), rounded to 4 decimal places
filters: only include rows where capital column indicates a capital city
for countries with multiple capitals, keep only the one with maximum population
sub_questions: For each country, select the capital with largest population
Calculate average latitude of selected capitals

scale_issues: Population values appear to be very large (millions)
Latitude values range from -90 to 90 degrees

format_notes: Sample shows 11 columns but description says 10
Capital column contains values like 'primary', 'admin', 'minor' and empty strings

constraints: Each country should contribute exactly one capital city to the average
Only cities marked as capitals should be considered
Population values must be valid numbers for comparison
Latitude values must be within valid range (-90 to 90)
statistical_tests: Check for duplicate capital designations within countries
Check for outliers in population values
output_format_requirements: Result must be a single numeric value
Value must be rounded to 4 decimal places
Result should be a float representing average latitude
